WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.334
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.418 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

00:56.598 --> 00:59.100
Hey, slow down!

00:59.184 --> 01:00.602
My bad. Are you okay?

01:00.685 --> 01:03.021
If you need to use the bathroom,
we can stop for a bit.

01:03.104 --> 01:04.522
No, I'm fine.

01:04.606 --> 01:06.816
I'm not. I'm scared.

01:09.986 --> 01:11.988
All right, here we are.

01:13.490 --> 01:15.492
If I get a ticket because of you…

01:18.953 --> 01:21.081
Go to the bathroom while I get the papers.

01:21.164 --> 01:22.332
No, I'm fine.

01:23.041 --> 01:24.334
I'll drive you home.

01:24.417 --> 01:26.044
I'll get going.

01:26.127 --> 01:27.879
-Where?
-Bye.

01:28.755 --> 01:31.299
-What about my keys?
-They're in the car!

01:32.717 --> 01:33.718
What's up with him?

01:56.533 --> 01:59.953
SEON-A

02:18.805 --> 02:20.390
What's wrong?

02:20.473 --> 02:21.808
You want to go for a walk?

02:22.976 --> 02:25.103
Can't we stay in for tonight?

02:27.063 --> 02:28.064
Fine.

02:28.148 --> 02:29.566
Let's go.

02:32.443 --> 02:33.444
Come here.

02:42.328 --> 02:43.288
Mr. Librarian?

03:00.096 --> 03:03.266
What brings you all the way here
at this hour?

03:03.349 --> 03:04.893
I'm too late, aren't I?

03:04.976 --> 03:05.935
Not at all.

03:12.609 --> 03:15.403
Well, everyone did leave.

03:19.198 --> 03:23.411
I was about to take a walk with Gyeo-ul.

03:24.329 --> 03:27.707
If we're going the same way,
why don't we walk together?

03:28.583 --> 03:29.542
Sure.

03:33.504 --> 03:34.547
By the way,

03:35.673 --> 03:37.383
why are you sweating so much?

03:39.260 --> 03:42.305
Oh. It's a bit warm today.

03:44.599 --> 03:45.642
Is it?

03:47.727 --> 03:51.022
Do you really go for a jog
that early every day?

03:52.148 --> 03:54.400
You have such a diligent lifestyle.

03:54.984 --> 03:56.986
My eyes just open at that time.

03:58.321 --> 03:59.906
I actually have trouble sleeping.

04:00.531 --> 04:03.201
If that's the case,
you should keep your eyes closed.

04:03.284 --> 04:06.204
When you close your eyes again,
you naturally fall back asleep.

04:06.287 --> 04:08.873
I've slept up to 14 hours like that.

04:09.624 --> 04:11.459
-Fourteen hours?
-Yes.

04:11.542 --> 04:15.630
But back when I was working in Seoul,
I led a healthy lifestyle too.

04:16.923 --> 04:19.425
-I only said that because I was jealous.
-I see.

04:26.724 --> 04:28.226
I'll be going…

04:28.309 --> 04:29.185
that way now.

04:29.269 --> 04:30.937
Take care.

04:32.021 --> 04:32.897
You too.

04:32.981 --> 04:33.940
Thank you.

04:35.066 --> 04:36.567
Goodbye, Gyeo-ul.

04:40.571 --> 04:41.823
Mr. Librarian!

04:51.082 --> 04:52.166
Never mind.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.419
Goodbye.

04:55.086 --> 04:57.005
-Okay. Goodbye.
-Bye.

05:00.842 --> 05:01.759
Let's go.

05:01.843 --> 05:05.513
ANGOK CATHOLIC CHURCH

05:05.596 --> 05:07.557
As if I can wake up early in the morning.

05:08.433 --> 05:10.018
Right, Gyeo-ul?

05:15.857 --> 05:16.899
Good morning.

05:16.983 --> 05:18.318
Ms. Lee!

05:19.736 --> 05:21.863
I thought I'd get some exercise too.

05:21.946 --> 05:22.989
Really?

05:25.158 --> 05:26.617
Slow down.

05:27.285 --> 05:28.536
You'll tire yourself out.

05:29.037 --> 05:30.163
I see.

05:31.706 --> 05:34.625
You don't even sound like
you're out of breath.

05:45.261 --> 05:48.056
CENTRAL ANGOK

05:51.768 --> 05:52.977
Stop it.

05:53.061 --> 05:55.313
I need some sleep.

05:55.396 --> 05:57.231
You should sleep too.

05:59.776 --> 06:01.903
Come on, I can do this.

06:03.905 --> 06:05.073
No, I can't.

06:05.156 --> 06:06.991
There must be some soju left.

06:12.080 --> 06:13.164
Ms. Lee.

06:14.290 --> 06:15.666
Good morning.

06:15.750 --> 06:17.502
You really came.

06:17.585 --> 06:19.253
It felt good to jog in the morning.

06:20.046 --> 06:22.090
In that case…

06:22.965 --> 06:25.551
shall we meet at the library
every morning for a jog?

06:26.260 --> 06:27.303
Every morning?

06:27.386 --> 06:30.389
I planned out some decent routes for us.

06:34.685 --> 06:37.313
But since it's very early in the morning,

06:37.396 --> 06:39.315
shorter routes would be better, right?

06:40.108 --> 06:41.400
Definitely.

06:43.528 --> 06:46.948
But still, you really don't have to
change your route for me.

06:47.031 --> 06:49.200
We can take the route you take,
Mr. Librarian.

06:50.368 --> 06:51.786
It's Dae-bum.

06:53.079 --> 06:54.038
Sorry?

06:54.622 --> 06:56.290
My name is Dae-bum.

06:56.874 --> 06:57.917
Yeo-reum.

07:03.464 --> 07:04.423
Okay.

07:13.724 --> 07:15.268
Gosh, I'm drained.

07:21.816 --> 07:23.901
I think he would like this.

07:25.736 --> 07:26.863
Yeo-reum!

07:29.157 --> 07:30.867
Are you inside, Yeo-reum?

07:32.118 --> 07:32.994
Ms. Jung!

07:33.578 --> 07:35.746
Gosh, there you are.

07:35.830 --> 07:36.956
Hello.

07:39.083 --> 07:39.959
Ms. Jung!

07:40.042 --> 07:41.794
What brings you here?

07:42.378 --> 07:43.671
You should come in.

07:43.754 --> 07:45.506
It's fine. I need to get going.

07:45.590 --> 07:46.591
I see.

07:47.300 --> 07:48.342
Actually,

07:48.426 --> 07:49.594
I…

07:50.428 --> 07:53.514
have a favor to ask you.

07:53.598 --> 07:54.724
What is it?

07:55.475 --> 07:57.101
You can ask me.

07:57.185 --> 08:01.647
Someone I know has a vacation home
by Dongcheon Valley.

08:02.190 --> 08:07.820
I was wondering if you would be willing
to go there to spend some time with Bom.

08:07.904 --> 08:09.030
Me?

08:10.156 --> 08:12.325
That young girl went through a lot.

08:12.909 --> 08:16.537
But I haven't done anything for her
as her grandmother.

08:17.914 --> 08:20.541
This isn't a favor. It's a gift.

08:21.042 --> 08:23.127
I'm so thankful to hear you say that.

08:23.211 --> 08:25.421
I get to go on a vacation thanks to you.

08:26.088 --> 08:27.215
Thank you.

08:29.175 --> 08:30.426
-Dae-bum.
-Yes?

08:30.968 --> 08:31.802
Dae-bum.

08:31.886 --> 08:32.970
Get over here.

08:36.891 --> 08:37.975
Look at this.

08:39.143 --> 08:40.269
A NEW INTERPRETATION OF QUANTUM PHYSICS
TURNS THE WORLD UPSIDE DOWN

08:40.353 --> 08:42.688
-This?
-Professor Lee is amazing.

08:42.772 --> 08:44.065
He's incredible.

08:45.650 --> 08:46.776
Come here.

08:46.859 --> 08:48.444
-What?
-Come here.

08:48.528 --> 08:50.071
-What's this?
-Goodness!

08:50.154 --> 08:51.447
Why?

08:52.156 --> 08:54.575
-What's wrong?
-You had sand on you.

08:54.659 --> 08:56.577
Oh, I see.

08:57.870 --> 09:00.498
Why are you being so fussy
about me touching you?

09:01.374 --> 09:02.583
Sorry.

09:47.878 --> 09:48.963
Hey.

09:50.840 --> 09:51.924
Hello.

10:08.774 --> 10:12.528
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

10:12.612 --> 10:13.613
Yeo-reum.

10:13.696 --> 10:15.489
COMMUNITY CENTER

10:18.451 --> 10:19.994
Are you leaving already?

10:20.620 --> 10:21.662
Yes.

10:24.582 --> 10:25.875
By any chance…

10:27.084 --> 10:30.796
are you going to have dinner--
I mean, are you busy tonight?

10:31.464 --> 10:33.966
Why? Do you want to see a movie?

10:34.467 --> 10:36.052
-A movie?
-Pardon?

10:40.014 --> 10:41.682
What I meant was…

10:41.766 --> 10:45.061
There's actually a movie
that I really wanted to see.

10:45.144 --> 10:47.688
And it just got released
in the theaters today.

10:47.772 --> 10:49.106
I see.

10:52.610 --> 10:54.320
-Do you want to come with--
-Should we watch--

10:57.073 --> 10:59.784
If it's okay with you.

11:00.451 --> 11:01.827
Should we?

11:05.456 --> 11:07.041
-This must be heavy.
-It's fine.

11:07.124 --> 11:08.626
-Let me help.
-No, it's heavy.

11:10.461 --> 11:11.671
I'm so sorry.

11:11.754 --> 11:13.506
It's fine. They're heavy.

11:16.550 --> 11:20.596
And I already have the tickets
for the movie.

11:20.679 --> 11:22.098
Already? Give that to me.

11:22.181 --> 11:23.307
This is heavy.

11:24.683 --> 11:26.102
-You can carry this.
-Okay.

11:45.579 --> 11:48.457
-Bom, any plans for the summer?
-I don't know. None of your business.

11:48.541 --> 11:50.126
-Yeo-reum!
-Yeo-reum!

11:51.836 --> 11:52.711
Skipping classes?

11:52.795 --> 11:54.547
What do you mean, "skipping"?

11:54.630 --> 11:56.048
Our summer break started today.

11:56.132 --> 11:57.216
-Already?
-Yes.

11:58.259 --> 12:00.177
Every day is summer break for me, so…

12:00.261 --> 12:01.595
How unfortunate though.

12:01.679 --> 12:06.225
I honestly was determined
to go to school diligently this time.

12:06.934 --> 12:09.520
But why do you keep smiling
while saying that?

12:09.603 --> 12:10.813
Mind your own business.

12:11.897 --> 12:13.232
Yeo-reum.

12:13.315 --> 12:16.610
I saw Grandma
packing up some stuff for you.

12:16.694 --> 12:18.654
Yes. I got them.

12:19.321 --> 12:21.407
Did she mention anything else?

12:22.199 --> 12:25.453
She said we should go somewhere together.

12:26.203 --> 12:28.038
Really? Like a trip?

12:28.122 --> 12:30.791
Seriously? I've been wanting
to go on a trip too.

12:30.875 --> 12:31.750
Where to, though?

12:31.834 --> 12:33.210
The beach? The mountains?

12:33.794 --> 12:35.754
Your grandma said that her acquaintance

12:35.838 --> 12:38.007
has a summer home in Dongcheon.

12:38.090 --> 12:38.966
Dongcheon?

12:39.592 --> 12:40.759
Where's that?

12:40.843 --> 12:42.678
That's not important.
What should I prepare?

12:42.761 --> 12:46.265
Hey, why are you assuming
that you're coming with us?

12:46.348 --> 12:47.183
Right.

12:47.266 --> 12:49.101
Let's invite Dae-bum as well.

12:49.685 --> 12:50.978
-Wait…
-I'll talk him into it.

12:51.896 --> 12:53.439
Dae-bum!

12:55.191 --> 12:57.318
This isn't a playground.

12:57.401 --> 12:58.611
My bad.

13:08.454 --> 13:09.872
Hey, this is the valley in Dongcheon.

13:09.955 --> 13:11.582
It's so nice. Look.

13:11.665 --> 13:15.002
Stop making a fuss about it.
We can just go see it there.

13:15.085 --> 13:16.462
I said I don't want to see it.

13:16.545 --> 13:17.755
Hey, guys.

13:18.589 --> 13:21.926
I actually have plans tonight.

13:22.635 --> 13:23.761
I'll see you later.

13:24.386 --> 13:25.304
Plans?

13:25.387 --> 13:27.139
Who would you spend time with besides us?

13:27.723 --> 13:29.808
Okay, Yeo-reum. We'll get going then.

13:30.559 --> 13:32.770
-Take care.
-Good luck.

13:33.395 --> 13:35.981
-What should we buy for the trip?
-How about meat?

13:42.905 --> 13:45.157
-Let's go have dinner.
-Sorry, Ji-yeong.

13:46.200 --> 13:48.160
I have plans tonight.

13:49.787 --> 13:51.247
With Yeo-reum?

13:51.330 --> 13:52.373
Yes.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.552
-Ahn Dae-bum.
-Yes?

14:04.635 --> 14:07.846
I'm not just a friend to you. Right?

14:09.765 --> 14:10.891
No.

14:17.982 --> 14:19.358
Ji-yeong, that hurts.

14:23.487 --> 14:26.824
I'm also starting to hurt because of you.

14:38.586 --> 14:40.546
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

14:40.629 --> 14:42.089
ANGOK PUBLIC LIBRARY

14:53.309 --> 14:54.602
Yeo-reum.

14:57.271 --> 14:58.689
Let me lock up real quick.

14:58.772 --> 15:00.399
Take your time.

15:08.324 --> 15:10.034
Shall we go then?

15:10.117 --> 15:10.951
Okay.

15:11.035 --> 15:12.828
Did I keep you waiting?

15:12.912 --> 15:15.205
Not at all. I just left the library.

15:18.459 --> 15:19.752
Pathetic.

15:36.769 --> 15:38.187
There are a lot of trees and…

15:43.901 --> 15:45.027
Goodness.

15:45.569 --> 15:48.739
You should always check
whether you have the lights on or off.

15:48.822 --> 15:51.367
You're so clumsy.

15:58.415 --> 16:00.417
Make sure to keep the engine running.

16:01.627 --> 16:03.671
You should be thanking me.

16:03.754 --> 16:05.756
Who else would come
to jump your battery this late?

16:05.839 --> 16:08.300
And why would you call me,
not the insurance company?

16:08.384 --> 16:09.677
You're such a weirdo.

16:12.638 --> 16:14.223
Why are you so moody?

16:18.018 --> 16:19.478
Ji-yeong, are you crying?

16:22.064 --> 16:23.107
Hey.

16:27.403 --> 16:29.446
What happened?

16:30.531 --> 16:33.492
I don't know. I feel so pathetic.

16:35.327 --> 16:37.746
All right, Ji-yeong.

16:37.830 --> 16:39.915
Go ahead. Crying makes you feel better.

16:42.960 --> 16:45.045
Everything is so annoying.

16:48.424 --> 16:49.633
Gosh.

16:54.179 --> 16:55.139
It's fine.

16:55.222 --> 16:56.724
Get me some tissues.

16:56.807 --> 16:58.475
Tissue? In the car?

17:01.729 --> 17:03.647
-Bottom compartment!
-Found it.

17:13.323 --> 17:15.117
Enjoy the movie.

17:16.618 --> 17:17.745
Here.

17:19.413 --> 17:20.956
I'm sorry, but you can't go in.

17:21.749 --> 17:23.709
-Why not?
-The ticket isn't for today.

17:23.792 --> 17:25.294
It's for next week.

17:25.377 --> 17:27.296
This movie premieres next week.

17:27.379 --> 17:28.881
That can't be true.

17:28.964 --> 17:31.008
Take a look at the date.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.260
You're right.

17:37.556 --> 17:40.184
How did I miss that?

17:41.769 --> 17:44.188
-I'm sorry.
-It's okay. No problem.

17:49.068 --> 17:50.110
Then…

17:50.194 --> 17:53.113
Do you want to go have some
chicken and beer?

17:53.739 --> 17:55.032
Chicken and beer?

17:56.033 --> 17:57.159
Earlier at the library,

17:57.785 --> 18:01.121
I was actually going to ask you out
for chicken and beer.

18:03.499 --> 18:05.375
-Sounds good.
-All right.

18:06.043 --> 18:07.753
Let me look a place up.

18:10.464 --> 18:12.049
If we go that way,

18:13.008 --> 18:15.844
there's a really old place
that sells amazing fried chicken.

18:15.928 --> 18:17.721
And there's a place down that way

18:18.388 --> 18:20.432
where the interior is nice and spacious,

18:20.516 --> 18:23.393
but the chicken doesn't taste as good.

18:23.477 --> 18:26.772
And down that way,
there's a place with outdoor tables

18:26.855 --> 18:29.525
known for its refreshing beer.

18:30.192 --> 18:33.028
You've really done your research.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.572
Yes. Just in case.

18:36.990 --> 18:38.075
I…

18:39.368 --> 18:40.494
choose number three.

18:41.078 --> 18:43.205
Beer tends to vary
more in taste than chicken.

18:43.288 --> 18:45.332
I see.

18:45.415 --> 18:47.251
How long does it take to get there?

18:47.334 --> 18:48.585
About ten minutes.

18:48.669 --> 18:50.170
It's close.

18:53.924 --> 18:55.467
Why are you running?

18:55.968 --> 18:57.719
It takes ten minutes by running.

19:00.556 --> 19:01.932
Do you want to walk instead?

19:02.015 --> 19:03.600
No, it's fine. Let's run.

19:04.184 --> 19:05.686
It takes 30 minutes when you walk.

19:05.769 --> 19:07.771
Let's get there in five minutes then.

19:15.195 --> 19:16.488
It's amazing.

19:17.281 --> 19:19.324
The beer here is so refreshing.

19:21.243 --> 19:23.579
Who thought of eating
chicken and beer together?

19:26.123 --> 19:30.669
Whoever first discovered
chicken and beer deserves an award.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.422
Use this.

19:35.048 --> 19:36.175
Thank you.

19:37.342 --> 19:38.510
It's so tasty.

19:38.594 --> 19:39.720
CHOSEON CHICKEN

19:39.803 --> 19:41.388
Before I forget.

19:42.264 --> 19:43.765
I brought this.

19:44.933 --> 19:46.226
MYEONGJU

19:47.144 --> 19:48.270
What's that?

19:48.353 --> 19:49.521
Youth of Angok.

19:50.147 --> 19:51.773
It was released today.

19:51.857 --> 19:52.983
No way.

19:58.989 --> 20:00.115
Hold on.

20:00.866 --> 20:03.744
-Don't tell me you read it already.
-No, I haven't read it yet.

20:04.369 --> 20:05.454
That's a relief.

20:05.537 --> 20:08.290
You shouldn't read it though.
My writing is awful.

20:08.999 --> 20:10.000
It was okay.

20:10.500 --> 20:13.003
What? You said you haven't read it.

20:13.086 --> 20:14.546
I meant the photo, not the writing.

20:14.630 --> 20:17.341
I brought another copy so I can read it

20:17.424 --> 20:18.800
as soon as I get home.

20:18.884 --> 20:21.094
No, please don't read that.

20:21.178 --> 20:23.347
You'll be disappointed.

20:26.058 --> 20:28.185
You little prick.

20:28.685 --> 20:32.064
How dare you trip me?

20:32.147 --> 20:33.232
Mister.

20:33.815 --> 20:35.484
-Gosh.
-What's wrong with him?

20:36.693 --> 20:37.778
Are you okay?

20:38.695 --> 20:40.197
-Goodness.
-Let go!

20:40.280 --> 20:41.365
You bastard.

20:41.448 --> 20:43.408
Listen.

20:43.492 --> 20:44.660
I was only okay

20:44.743 --> 20:48.121
because I learned
how to fall safely in the Marine Corps.

20:48.205 --> 20:50.749
If it were anyone else,
they would've hit their head.

20:50.832 --> 20:52.251
You better watch out!

20:54.461 --> 20:55.545
Let go of me!

21:07.557 --> 21:08.934
Is something wrong?

21:11.019 --> 21:13.397
You're dead if you tell anyone
what happened today.

21:13.480 --> 21:14.523
Goodness.

21:14.606 --> 21:18.068
No one would believe that
the mighty Ji-yeong cried her eyes out.

21:23.573 --> 21:24.616
Thank you.

21:26.952 --> 21:27.995
What?

21:28.745 --> 21:30.789
You're all I've got.

21:35.961 --> 21:37.004
See you.

21:38.588 --> 21:41.341
If there's anything that's troubling you,
just tell me.

21:42.050 --> 21:43.844
Your existence is troubling me.

21:43.927 --> 21:46.430
Seriously? At least you seem better now,

21:46.513 --> 21:49.308
with that attitude back and all.

21:51.601 --> 21:52.728
Bye.

21:53.562 --> 21:55.230
Drive safely.

21:56.982 --> 21:58.150
I'm going.

22:07.492 --> 22:08.869
I'm all she has?

22:12.289 --> 22:13.623
Am I the only one?

22:19.504 --> 22:20.839
-Did you enjoy the food?
-Yes.

22:20.922 --> 22:23.050
-How much is it?
-I got it.

22:23.133 --> 22:24.134
It's okay.

22:24.217 --> 22:26.136
It's already been paid for.

22:27.262 --> 22:29.347
The guy who tripped earlier paid.

22:29.931 --> 22:31.016
Really?

22:39.941 --> 22:44.029
The beer was great,
and we got free chicken.

22:44.529 --> 22:45.781
What an amazing day.

22:49.034 --> 22:52.162
So, do you just not get angry?

22:53.705 --> 22:56.583
I've never seen you get angry.

23:00.253 --> 23:02.255
That was an aggravating moment earlier.

23:03.048 --> 23:06.426
Do you not get angry
or are you just holding it back?

23:08.345 --> 23:10.514
Anything can happen in life.

23:12.224 --> 23:13.892
That's how I try to understand them.

23:16.853 --> 23:19.022
So that I can keep living on.

23:25.612 --> 23:27.405
You're much more mature than I am.

23:28.365 --> 23:31.284
It's not easy for me to think like that.

23:35.622 --> 23:37.958
It takes a while for us
to get home, right?

23:39.126 --> 23:42.003
Why don't we kill some time
playing 21 questions?

23:42.963 --> 23:44.840
Did you say 21 questions?

23:44.923 --> 23:48.802
I'll probably be asking
all the questions, but…

23:48.885 --> 23:49.970
Okay.

23:52.806 --> 23:55.183
What's your favorite fruit?

23:56.059 --> 23:57.561
Apples are my favorite.

23:58.228 --> 24:00.230
You answered so quickly.

24:02.399 --> 24:03.400
Mine are…

24:03.483 --> 24:04.568
strawberries.

24:06.194 --> 24:07.445
Strawberries.

24:08.321 --> 24:09.781
Then…

24:09.865 --> 24:11.283
For my next question,

24:11.366 --> 24:13.451
who is your favorite…

24:14.035 --> 24:15.203
author?

24:17.205 --> 24:18.707
This is a hard one.

24:20.542 --> 24:21.793
Just off the top of your head.

24:22.586 --> 24:25.255
My favorite is Kim Ae-ran.

24:25.839 --> 24:26.882
I see.

24:26.965 --> 24:28.091
What about you?

24:28.175 --> 24:30.218
My favorite is Carl Sagan.

24:31.511 --> 24:34.347
I had a great time reading
Murmurs of Earth.

24:34.431 --> 24:36.558
The book suits you well.

24:37.642 --> 24:39.269
Let's ask our last questions.

24:40.562 --> 24:43.148
What's your favorite season?

24:43.231 --> 24:44.691
I love summer.

24:46.568 --> 24:48.445
I mean the season.

24:50.071 --> 24:51.281
I know.

24:51.907 --> 24:54.075
Summer is my favorite as well.

24:59.122 --> 25:02.167
Can I ask one more?

25:02.250 --> 25:03.376
Of course.

25:05.337 --> 25:06.755
When we first met,

25:07.464 --> 25:11.009
why did you not talk to me?

25:13.929 --> 25:15.555
Actually…

25:16.973 --> 25:20.894
I have trouble talking to strangers.

25:21.519 --> 25:22.604
That's why.

25:25.565 --> 25:29.361
Does that mean you feel
comfortable around me now?

25:29.444 --> 25:31.488
We talked a lot today.

25:32.280 --> 25:35.242
Maybe that's why my throat kind of hurts.

25:37.160 --> 25:39.037
I don't think you've talked that much.

25:48.505 --> 25:51.174
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO KILLED SEON-A

25:53.301 --> 25:54.386
What the heck?

25:54.469 --> 25:55.637
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO KILLED SEON-A

26:00.809 --> 26:02.060
YOU'RE THE ONE

26:03.561 --> 26:04.813
Are you okay?

26:04.896 --> 26:06.356
Excuse me, Yeo-reum.

26:06.940 --> 26:08.191
Dae-bum.

26:09.317 --> 26:10.485
Dae-bum!

26:37.762 --> 26:38.972
YOU'RE THE ONE

26:41.433 --> 26:42.726
WHO KILLED SEON-A

27:38.448 --> 27:40.158
Answer me!

27:41.242 --> 27:42.369
I don't know.

27:42.452 --> 27:45.330
How dare you lie in front of the police?

27:48.500 --> 27:49.501
Dae-bum.

27:50.001 --> 27:53.380
You've told us everything until now.
Why are you acting like this?

27:53.463 --> 27:56.424
You said you saw your dad run away
on your way home.

27:58.218 --> 27:59.302
Am I wrong?

28:00.095 --> 28:01.846
Dae-bum, look at me.

28:02.931 --> 28:05.141
I'm telling you to look at me.

28:10.230 --> 28:11.314
Tell me.

28:12.148 --> 28:14.275
You're actually happy she's dead,
aren't you?

28:15.819 --> 28:17.320
You hated her.

28:19.114 --> 28:20.198
Aren't I right?

28:23.576 --> 28:24.661
It's true.

28:25.412 --> 28:27.205
You're glad that your sister died.

28:31.584 --> 28:34.087
No, I'm not. That's not true.

28:34.170 --> 28:35.505
It's not!

28:39.551 --> 28:40.927
It's not true.

28:59.946 --> 29:01.489
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO KILLED SEON-A

29:20.759 --> 29:21.926
Dae-bum.

29:27.515 --> 29:28.683
Ahn Dae-bum.

29:38.151 --> 29:39.527
Hey, you're here.

29:40.111 --> 29:41.613
Who opened up the shutter doors?

29:42.280 --> 29:43.907
-Did you open it?
-No.

29:45.200 --> 29:46.910
Hurry up and pull it down.

29:49.329 --> 29:50.830
YOU'RE THE ONE

29:50.914 --> 29:52.665
What kind of lunatic did this?

29:52.749 --> 29:54.626
-Gosh.
-Someone made a mess again.

29:54.709 --> 29:55.794
"You're

29:55.877 --> 29:57.420
the one…

29:57.504 --> 29:59.464
WHO KILLED SEON-A

29:59.547 --> 30:02.175
…who killed Seon-a?"

30:02.759 --> 30:04.761
But it was Seon-a's dad who murdered her.

30:04.844 --> 30:05.678
Gosh.

30:05.762 --> 30:08.014
I think we should report this

30:08.097 --> 30:09.265
before it blows up.

30:09.349 --> 30:11.935
That's a bad idea.
Word will spread across town.

30:12.018 --> 30:14.020
That's not the issue here.

30:14.103 --> 30:15.688
Gosh, seriously.

30:15.772 --> 30:19.609
What did I do to Seon-a's family
to deserve this nonsense?

30:19.692 --> 30:22.111
Dad. Can you please watch your words?

30:23.738 --> 30:25.406
Dae-bum, that bastard.

30:25.490 --> 30:27.867
I took it easy on him
because I felt bad, but now…

30:27.951 --> 30:29.327
He's a victim.

30:30.328 --> 30:31.246
What?

30:31.746 --> 30:34.332
Dae-bum is the biggest victim here.

30:34.958 --> 30:36.626
I'm glad you brought that up.

30:37.669 --> 30:39.337
Did I kill his sister and his mom?

30:39.420 --> 30:43.341
Look what happened to my building
because of his family.

30:44.008 --> 30:46.094
I'm the victim here!

30:46.177 --> 30:48.638
-Dad.
-Sir, please calm down.

30:48.721 --> 30:51.391
Sir, I'll tell you what.

30:51.933 --> 30:54.018
I'll install CCTV there first.

30:54.102 --> 30:56.688
Yes, CCTV sounds great.

30:56.771 --> 30:59.190
You should've installed it sooner.

30:59.691 --> 31:00.984
Mu-cheol, thank you.

31:01.568 --> 31:03.444
I can always rely on you.

31:04.362 --> 31:05.697
Damn it.

31:05.780 --> 31:06.823
Yeo-reum.

31:10.702 --> 31:14.539
If you see anyone suspicious,
call me immediately.

31:16.624 --> 31:17.834
Okay.

31:17.917 --> 31:19.294
Hello, Professor Lee.

31:19.377 --> 31:21.671
-It's Park Cheol-hyeon from Naeil Daily.
-I don't do interviews.

31:21.754 --> 31:23.882
-I'm hanging up.
-Please hold on.

31:23.965 --> 31:26.175
In science forums,

31:26.259 --> 31:28.052
-the dissertation you wrote--
-I'm busy.

31:28.136 --> 31:30.972
-Goodbye.
-Professor Lee.

31:31.931 --> 31:32.849
Professor Lee.

31:33.766 --> 31:35.643
I think you should take a look at this.

31:36.644 --> 31:38.730
It's a post
from our school's online forum.

31:39.480 --> 31:40.940
What's this?

31:41.524 --> 31:45.820
Everyone's talking about
how you stole someone else's idea.

31:45.904 --> 31:47.363
"Stole"?

31:47.447 --> 31:51.159
Look at all this nonsense.

31:51.784 --> 31:54.120
I think this will only get worse

31:54.203 --> 31:56.289
unless Dae-bum shows up himself.

31:56.372 --> 31:58.541
The school president wants to call
the institutional review board.

31:59.250 --> 32:00.877
Institutional review board?

32:01.586 --> 32:03.087
What happens then?

32:03.171 --> 32:04.631
If things go wrong,

32:04.714 --> 32:07.175
it's over for him in his field of studies.

32:07.258 --> 32:09.218
Buying ideas from another person

32:09.302 --> 32:10.887
is a huge moral issue.

32:11.387 --> 32:14.015
This can also cause harm
to Dae-bum if things--

32:14.098 --> 32:16.517
-Even Dae-bum?
-Yes.

32:17.435 --> 32:19.979
That's why he has to come
to the board meeting

32:20.063 --> 32:21.606
and explain what happened.

32:22.607 --> 32:23.733
I'm begging you.

32:28.154 --> 32:29.322
All right.

32:29.864 --> 32:32.700
I'll speak to Dae-bum about this
and let you know.

32:34.494 --> 32:35.620
Hello.

32:37.455 --> 32:39.624
Did Dae-bum come in today?

32:40.208 --> 32:41.250
"Dae-bum"?

32:42.669 --> 32:44.420
He's not here yet.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.092
By any chance…

32:50.385 --> 32:52.387
did something happen
when he was with you last night?

32:55.723 --> 32:56.683
Well…

32:58.935 --> 33:02.063
Did we really have to buy this much?

33:02.146 --> 33:04.482
It's a day trip, not a neighborhood party.

33:04.565 --> 33:06.192
My bad. It's just happened.

33:07.110 --> 33:09.904
It may look like much,
but we'll go through these in a flash.

33:09.988 --> 33:10.989
Gosh.

33:13.408 --> 33:15.201
Hey, where are you going?

33:15.702 --> 33:17.370
Are you not coming in?

33:17.453 --> 33:18.454
This is my home.

33:18.538 --> 33:20.540
-Here?
-Yes.

33:22.375 --> 33:23.543
Come on in.

33:27.797 --> 33:29.632
You can put it over here.

33:33.177 --> 33:34.262
Hey.

33:34.345 --> 33:36.347
Is this place really your home?

33:36.431 --> 33:38.057
No. It's my aunt's.

33:38.599 --> 33:39.642
My homeroom teacher?

33:40.435 --> 33:41.644
You knew?

33:41.728 --> 33:44.856
Everyone in our school knows.

33:44.939 --> 33:47.316
You guys always meet
behind the teacher's office.

33:48.026 --> 33:48.985
So everyone knows.

33:50.987 --> 33:52.155
But I didn't know homeroom…

33:53.156 --> 33:56.367
I mean, your aunt, was this rich.

33:56.451 --> 33:58.619
Well, it's a bit complicated.

33:58.703 --> 33:59.704
Come here.

33:59.787 --> 34:02.707
My dad bought this place
so she can keep her eyes on me.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.084
You can sit here.

34:07.837 --> 34:10.798
It must be suffocating
to live with your aunt.

34:11.382 --> 34:12.884
But my aunt doesn't live here.

34:12.967 --> 34:13.885
What?

34:13.968 --> 34:15.887
So you have this huge place
all to yourself?

34:16.763 --> 34:19.307
Actually, I only use the first floor.

34:19.390 --> 34:20.349
Why?

34:20.850 --> 34:22.769
No idea. You rest up here.

34:22.852 --> 34:24.771
It's fine. Let's organize it together.

34:24.854 --> 34:26.189
Thank you.

34:29.442 --> 34:31.277
Hey, what's this?

34:32.028 --> 34:34.697
Why is this huge refrigerator
completely empty?

34:34.781 --> 34:36.616
Don't you like cooking?

34:36.699 --> 34:39.160
I cook for others, not for myself.

34:39.243 --> 34:40.953
I don't usually cook.

34:44.373 --> 34:47.210
Bom, if you're going to help,
can you peel the pears?

34:49.754 --> 34:51.380
Hey, I think someone's here.

34:58.888 --> 35:00.723
Why are you here so suddenly?

35:01.349 --> 35:03.810
I told you the English teacher
will be here today.

35:05.228 --> 35:06.312
What's all this?

35:07.021 --> 35:08.189
And why is she here?

35:09.315 --> 35:10.650
Auntie, actually…

35:11.442 --> 35:12.527
Heo Jae-hun.

35:12.610 --> 35:13.611
Let's talk outside.

35:13.694 --> 35:14.987
-Thomas.
-Yes?

35:20.076 --> 35:21.619
Bom, sorry. Give me a second.

35:26.833 --> 35:27.959
Heo Jae-hun!

35:28.459 --> 35:30.294
What on earth is wrong with you?

35:30.378 --> 35:31.420
Tell me.

35:31.504 --> 35:33.172
How many times did I tell you?

35:33.256 --> 35:36.217
You can't be doing this!
Think of your mom and dad!

35:36.300 --> 35:38.177
Come to your senses!

36:27.518 --> 36:29.687
Get up. Let's get you to a doctor.

36:32.523 --> 36:34.066
Come on, get up.

36:37.653 --> 36:38.779
No.

36:39.822 --> 36:41.574
I'm okay.

36:43.701 --> 36:44.827
Fine.

36:46.329 --> 36:48.539
Do whatever you want. I don't care.

36:58.799 --> 37:01.093
I warned you. I won't tell you twice.

37:02.720 --> 37:04.639
I'll be going now, Jae-hun.

37:04.722 --> 37:05.556
Hey.

37:06.265 --> 37:07.225
Listen.

37:07.808 --> 37:09.518
I don't know what you're up to,

37:09.602 --> 37:11.437
but don't call him ever again.

37:14.148 --> 37:15.191
Heo Jae-hun.

37:16.400 --> 37:18.069
Do you not like hanging out with me?

37:18.152 --> 37:19.237
What did you say?

37:20.863 --> 37:23.991
I do. I love hanging out with you.

37:24.951 --> 37:28.037
See? He's the one who keeps
chasing me around.

37:28.120 --> 37:29.121
You little…

37:29.205 --> 37:30.957
Hey, do you want to get expelled?

37:31.040 --> 37:32.375
Bom, I'll come with you.

37:32.458 --> 37:34.168
Jae-hun! Where do you think you're going?

37:34.252 --> 37:36.379
I'm going to tell your dad everything.

37:36.462 --> 37:37.672
Suit yourself.

37:40.299 --> 37:43.261
She's a very bad Auntie.

37:43.844 --> 37:45.179
I heard everything too.

37:45.846 --> 37:47.098
Thomas.

38:00.653 --> 38:02.029
-Nurse Kim.
-Yes.

38:02.113 --> 38:03.614
Give him an injection.

38:03.698 --> 38:05.741
-Okay.
-Make sure you get the shot.

38:06.575 --> 38:08.494
-Okay.
-Come this way.

38:16.460 --> 38:17.962
How is he?

38:18.045 --> 38:21.924
Our bodies are smart.
You might think you've forgotten about it,

38:23.009 --> 38:25.136
but they don't forget traumas so easily.

38:26.512 --> 38:28.306
His mind needs to rest, okay?

38:28.389 --> 38:29.307
Of course.

38:30.725 --> 38:33.227
Just let him do whatever he wants to do.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.396
All we can do is just wait.

38:35.479 --> 38:36.605
Lie down and relax.

38:37.273 --> 38:40.401
He's not doing so great, is he?

38:40.484 --> 38:42.820
No. Not too great.

38:44.155 --> 38:46.282
I'll prescribe more medicine,

38:46.365 --> 38:48.951
so make sure he takes it regularly.

38:49.035 --> 38:50.328
Okay, I will.

38:50.411 --> 38:51.746
By the way,

38:52.788 --> 38:55.082
when are you two getting married?

38:55.166 --> 38:56.459
Next in line can come in.

38:56.542 --> 38:59.003
Gosh, I told you we aren't together.

39:00.504 --> 39:02.840
He's just bad at expressing his feelings.

39:04.759 --> 39:06.135
Hold on.

39:06.844 --> 39:08.721
Who the hell drew that graffiti?

39:21.776 --> 39:23.069
Die, Seon-a.

39:23.944 --> 39:26.447
Kill Seon-a. Seon-a dies.

39:26.530 --> 39:28.616
Kill Seon-a. Seon-a dies.

39:28.699 --> 39:30.409
Kill Seon-a! Seon-a dies!

39:31.035 --> 39:32.453
Kill Seon-a! Seon-a dies!

39:33.496 --> 39:34.789
Kill Seon-a!

39:34.872 --> 39:37.917
-Die Seon-a!
-She's not Seon-a, Geun-ho!

39:38.000 --> 39:39.543
-Please.
-Seon-a die.

39:39.627 --> 39:41.629
Get yourself together, please.

39:42.338 --> 39:44.632
Geun-ho. Look at me.

39:44.715 --> 39:47.134
If you do that again,
I'll have to call the cops.

39:47.218 --> 39:49.762
The cops are so scary!

39:49.845 --> 39:51.222
Geun-ho.

39:51.305 --> 39:53.349
-The cops are so scary!
-Geun-ho.

39:53.432 --> 39:55.684
-Seon-a is in danger.
-Calm down.

39:55.768 --> 39:57.144
It's okay, Geun-ho.

40:02.274 --> 40:03.317
Ji-yeong.

40:06.112 --> 40:07.279
You were…

40:10.741 --> 40:12.952
friends with my sister.

40:16.664 --> 40:17.790
Did you like her?

40:20.084 --> 40:21.794
Friends, my foot.

40:21.877 --> 40:24.338
If she was at the top,
I was at rock bottom.

40:30.010 --> 40:31.512
I hated her.

40:38.477 --> 40:40.896
Father always scolded me…

40:45.317 --> 40:47.486
because of her.

41:17.016 --> 41:20.019
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

41:21.979 --> 41:24.690
What brings you here?

41:30.321 --> 41:32.031
So this is what your home is like.

41:32.656 --> 41:33.866
I'll take a seat.

41:37.620 --> 41:38.621
So…

41:39.830 --> 41:41.665
What about Dae-bum?

41:42.374 --> 41:45.085
He was medicated at the hospital

41:45.169 --> 41:47.630
and he's now home getting some rest.

41:47.713 --> 41:48.923
The hospital?

41:55.179 --> 41:56.263
Yeo-reum.

41:57.640 --> 42:00.559
You've heard what happened
in this place, right?

42:02.394 --> 42:04.772
Yes, Bom told me.

42:06.941 --> 42:09.109
When Dae-bum's sister died here,

42:09.693 --> 42:11.946
do you know who found her first?

42:15.115 --> 42:16.283
It was Dae-bum.

42:17.868 --> 42:20.829
The first one to find his mother
when she had killed herself…

42:22.456 --> 42:23.707
was Dae-bum as well.

42:25.167 --> 42:26.710
For him,

42:27.336 --> 42:30.881
the fact that you live in this building
is taking a toll on him.

42:30.965 --> 42:32.758
It keeps reminding him of his past.

42:34.176 --> 42:38.389
He thinks he caused
all of his family's deaths.

42:41.016 --> 42:42.434
What about Bom's hospital bill?

42:43.269 --> 42:44.853
Do you know who paid for it?

42:45.729 --> 42:47.648
Hospital bill? I thought…

42:48.190 --> 42:52.069
Because you were distressed about
Bom's hospital bills,

42:52.736 --> 42:55.489
he called his old professor

42:55.573 --> 42:57.324
and sold his thesis to him.

42:58.075 --> 42:59.535
For the hospital bill.

43:02.496 --> 43:06.333
Thanks to that, the professor
that helped Dae-bum is in trouble.

43:07.459 --> 43:10.796
If Dae-bum doesn't go to Seoul
this instant,

43:11.505 --> 43:14.008
everything will be ruined.

43:14.091 --> 43:15.509
Why did this happen?

43:17.469 --> 43:18.387
Yeo-reum.

43:19.638 --> 43:20.889
Do you like Dae-bum?

43:22.308 --> 43:23.309
Sorry?

43:23.392 --> 43:25.227
I actually don't even care anymore.

43:25.853 --> 43:28.230
I don't care how you feel about him.

43:28.314 --> 43:30.733
I absolutely despise the fact

43:30.816 --> 43:34.653
that Dae-bum is getting worse
because of you.

43:36.030 --> 43:39.241
Do you know how hard it was
for him to recover as much as he did?

43:40.200 --> 43:42.745
He keeps running because he can't sleep.

43:43.829 --> 43:45.289
He's always alone.

43:45.914 --> 43:47.458
That's how he held up.

43:47.958 --> 43:50.961
He held onto his life
trying his best not to break down.

43:51.795 --> 43:54.006
But all of that fell apart today.

43:55.341 --> 43:57.134
He shut himself off in his room.

43:58.844 --> 43:59.970
I don't even know

44:00.721 --> 44:03.515
when he'll be
able to leave his room again.

44:09.229 --> 44:10.397
I'm sorry.

44:10.481 --> 44:13.442
I don't need that. Anyone can apologize.

44:14.360 --> 44:15.486
Yeo-reum.

44:16.737 --> 44:18.405
Can you take responsibility?

44:20.366 --> 44:23.869
Can you take responsibility
for Dae-bum's life?

44:26.080 --> 44:27.331
I can.

44:27.998 --> 44:30.584
I always have, and always will.

44:33.253 --> 44:34.588
For you,

44:36.048 --> 44:38.592
this might be
just a summer fling by the beach,

44:38.676 --> 44:40.552
but that's not the case for me.

44:40.636 --> 44:42.471
It's not like that.

44:44.890 --> 44:47.518
If it's not, then help me.

44:49.186 --> 44:51.146
If you're not going to leave this place,

44:51.230 --> 44:53.816
please help me
so that he can leave this place.

44:56.235 --> 44:57.486
I'm asking you a favor.

45:01.407 --> 45:02.533
Just this once.

45:33.480 --> 45:35.065
Will you be okay?

45:36.942 --> 45:39.403
I'll have to beg for her forgiveness.

45:40.571 --> 45:41.697
Of course, you will.

45:43.824 --> 45:45.701
Thank you, Bom.

45:47.619 --> 45:48.704
For what?

45:50.539 --> 45:51.540
For everything.

45:54.293 --> 45:56.128
I'm jealous

45:57.045 --> 45:58.213
of what you can do.

45:58.797 --> 46:00.299
You're jealous of me?

46:00.966 --> 46:02.134
I'm jealous of you.

46:02.217 --> 46:04.386
-You are?
-Yes.

46:05.387 --> 46:06.722
You're rich.

46:11.643 --> 46:12.853
The way I see it,

46:13.687 --> 46:15.564
you're way richer than I am.

46:17.691 --> 46:20.486
You have Ha-neul and your grandma.

46:30.120 --> 46:30.954
Hey.

46:31.538 --> 46:34.249
What if she really gets me expelled?

46:34.917 --> 46:37.169
Go back home
and put in a good word for me.

46:39.087 --> 46:41.256
I'll just say I'll quit school too then.

46:43.509 --> 46:44.927
Whatever.

48:30.198 --> 48:33.076
If only I didn't move into
in the billiard club,

48:33.160 --> 48:35.871
you wouldn't have had to
go through all this.

48:35.954 --> 48:38.165
You know it's not your fault.

48:38.248 --> 48:42.127
I'm truly happy that you came to Angok.

48:42.210 --> 48:45.297
I don't want any more sadness in my life.

48:45.380 --> 48:47.466
If someone comes
to draw graffiti again, bite them.

48:48.300 --> 48:49.843
All right. Take care.

48:49.926 --> 48:52.179
The graffiti must be that bastard's doing.

48:52.262 --> 48:53.639
We've installed CCTV, so…

48:53.722 --> 48:54.765
Who the hell are you?

48:54.848 --> 48:55.974
…we'll catch them next time.

48:56.683 --> 49:01.146
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
